**GULD BROWSER INSTALLATION:**

Guld Browser requires the following software:

- NPM – Node package manager
- Node - (version 5 or greater)
- ledger-cli - (version 3 or greater)
- pgp - (version 2.1 or greater) only required if there are no gpg keys



Windows Installation

1. See if you already have NPM installed (you need version 5 or greater):
  1. pen the Windows Command Prompt
  2. type: npm –v  (If installed you will see something similar to 5.0.3
2. See if you already have Node installed:
  1. pen the Windows Command Prompt
  2. type: node –v  (If installed you will see something similar to v6.10.0


3. Node/NPM are installed together. If you do not have it installed follow these instructions:
  1. Go to the nodejs website: [https://nodejs.org/en/](https://nodejs.org/en/)
  2. Download the Windows installer from the  [**Nodes.js® web site**](http://nodejs.org/) **.**
  3. Run the installer (the .msi file you downloaded in the previous step.)
 4. Follow the prompts in the installer (Accept the license agreement, click the NEXT button a bunch of times and accept the default installation settings

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)
  5. **Restart your computer.**  You won&#39;t be able to run Node.js® until you restart your computer.
  6. Re-run steps 1 and 2 to confirm that you have installed Node and NPM

4. From the Windows Command Prompt Install ledger-cli:
Type: npm install ledger-cli -g

5. From the Windows Command Prompt Install gpg:
Type: npm install gpg -g


Mac Installation

1. See if you already have NPM installed:
  1. pen Terminal Prompt
  2. type: npm –v  (If installed you will see something similar to 5.0.3

2. See if you already have Node installed:
  1. pen Terminal Prompt
  2. type: node –v  (If installed you will see something similar to v6.10.0


3. Node/NPM are installed together. If you do not have it installed follow these instructions:
  1. Node requires 2 other applications before installation:
    1. XCode  (used for development on a Mac).  XCode is free and you can find it in the  [Apple App Store](https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/xcode/id497799835?mt=12).
    2. Homebrew (package manager for the Mac).
      1.  open Terminal Prompt
      2. type: ruby -e &quot;$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)&quot;
  2. Install Node/NPM:
    1. pen Terminal Prompt
    2. type: brew install node
    3. Re-run steps 1 and 2 to confirm that you have installed Node and NPM
4. From the Terminal Prompt Install ledger-cli:
Type: npm install ledger-cli -g

5. From the Terminal Prompt Install gpg:
Type: npm install gpg -g
